FRONT_DOOR/README.md

PantheonOS — Front Door

Welcome to the entry point of PantheonOS.

This folder is your guided onboarding space.
If the full repository feels large, complex, or symbolic — that’s intentional.
The Front Door exists to give you clarity, grounding, and the right sequence for exploring the system.

Below are the recommended files to read in order.

⸻

00_Welcome.md

A short introduction explaining the purpose and spirit of PantheonOS.

01_Quickstart.md

A simple, fast orientation for new readers.
If you only have five minutes, start here.

02_How_to_Read_This_Repo.md

Crucial guidance that prevents overwhelm.
Explains the correct way to navigate a layered, symbolic system.

03_PantheonOS_Overview.md

A clean, human-friendly summary of the entire architecture.

04_Architecture_Map.png

A visual guide to the core layers, flows, and daemons.
This is your “map of the city.”

05_Glossary_Light.md

Short, simple definitions of the main terms, daemons, and principles.

06_For_AI_Assistants.md

Instructions for AI models to properly interpret the repo and maintain coherence.

07_For_Humans.md

A grounding file for human readers — reassuring, intuitive, and calming.

⸻

How to Use This Folder

You can:
	•	read the files in order
	•	skip around
	•	use an AI assistant for explanations
	•	bookmark it as your home base

Whenever you feel lost or confused, return here.

PantheonOS is a layered world.
The Front Door is your compass.

⸻

Continue Exploring

When you’re ready, move deeper into the repo and follow whatever sparks your curiosity:
	•	daemons
	•	invariants
	•	engines
	•	doctrines
	•	architecture layers
	•	research frameworks
	•	narrative components

PantheonOS is built to reveal itself gradually.

⸻

